getFilters

java.util.List<Filter> getFilters()
                                  throws VINException
Get the filters that apply for the Vin instance this manager is passed to.

Returns:
The list of applicable Filters, the order in which those are returned defines the order they will have in the filter selection Ui display.
Throws:
VINException

getInitialFilterIds

java.util.Set<java.lang.String> getInitialFilterIds()
                                                    throws VINException
Get which filters are activated at taskflow load. This is optional (can return null if no filters are activated), and will be called only at taskflow initialization time.

Returns:
The list of ids for the filters that are active at Vin startup time.
Throws:
VINException

createFilterProcessor

FilterProcessor createFilterProcessor(java.util.List<Filter> filters)
                                      throws VINException
Create the object that will actually be used to filter entities from the model.

Parameters:
filters - The filters for which the FilterProcessor should be created. This will always be a subset of (or equal to) the list obtained through getFilter().
Returns:
The FilterProcessor to be used to filter entities in Vin.
Throws:
VINException
